defendant to bail in the sum of N25,000 with one surety in like sum. He then adjourned the case to December 21 for hearing. Vanguard News Nigeria A 43-year-old dismissed Police officer, Christopher Omeleze, attached to the state Traffic Division, Ikeja, Lagos, has been arraigned before an Ikeja Magistrate’s Court, for allegedly taking bribe from a motorist. September 22, 2013 In "News" A teenager, Alade Mujeed, was on Monday arraigned in an Ile-Ife Magistrates’ Court in Osun for allegedly stealing an Infinix Hot5 mobile phone worth N35,000 in an examination hall. December 23, 2019 In "News" Onozure Dania A 26-year-old house help, Happiness Michael, who allegedly stole her employer's jewelries and cash worth N1,060,000, was on Thursday brought before an Igbosere Magistrate Court sitting in Lagos. Michael is arraigned by the police on a two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing. The police prosecutor, Insp. Ingobo Emby… October 24, 2019 In "News"